						               													<description>This game is a Bible trivia version of Bingo. But instead of the letters of &amp;quot;bingo&amp;quot; for the columns, the columns of this game are A, M, E, N and !. According to the rules of the game: the exclamation point column is to be identified as the &amp;quot;Halleluiah&amp;quot; column. Another difference is that the moderator does not simply call out squares to be covered on the player's card, but will indicate a column and read a question from one of five question cards. If you know the answer and have the answer on your card, then you cover that square. For instance, the moderator might say: &amp;quot;Column A. Who killed Goliath?&amp;quot; If you have David in your card's Column A, you would cover it. The free square is known in this game as &amp;quot;Free Salvation by Jesus.&amp;quot; The first player to complete a horizontal, vertical or diagonal row calls out &amp;quot;Amen!&amp;quot; and wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
